                    <div class="detail-paragraph p-5">
                        <p class="text-gray-500">The CCC is a multi-sectoral national platform to coordinate and facilitate Global Fund activities to fight against HIV/AIDS, TB and malaria in Cambodia.The CCC is comprised of representatives of stakeholder constituencies represented at the national level. The mandate of the CCC is to mobilize a national multi-sectoral response to develop and submit proposals to the Global Fund to scale up the fight against HIV/AIDS, TB and malaria, and to oversee and support the implementation of activities that are initiated by the CCC in line with national program priorities and supported by the Global Fund.The purpose of the CCC is to enhance the performance of the Global Fund activities in Cambodia in partnership with stakeholder constituencies, to promote efficient program implementation, to avoid duplication by harmonizing Global Fund activities with other programs throughout Cambodia, and to strengthen coordination among stakeholder constituencies. The CCC is a multi-sectoral national platform to coordinate and facilitate Global Fund activities to fight against HIV/AIDS, TB and malaria in Cambodia.The CCC is comprised of representatives of stakeholder constituencies represented at the national level. The mandate of the CCC is to mobilize a national multi-sectoral response to develop and submit proposals to the Global Fund to scale up the fight against HIV/AIDS, Test.</p><br>

